OL,6,FIn the first interview the university
OL,7,Fhas done since, Vice Chancellor Wendy
OL,8,FLarner said: "My thoughts go out to
OL,9,Fthe Foulkes family.
OL,11,F"Every life matters. Mared's life
OL,12,Fmatters. She was a very valued member
OL,13,Fof the School of Pharmacy, of our
OL,14,Funiversity. We have learned, we've
OL,15,Flearned from Mared's death. We could
OL,16,Fhave done better.
OL,18,F"My predecessor did apologise to the
OL,19,Ffamily for the mistakes that were
OL,20,Fmade."
