OL,3,CUniversity admits it 'could have done
OL,4,Cbetter' after student took own life
OL,6,FNine months before Mared died, she had
OL,7,Fvisited University Support Services to
OL,8,Fdiscuss her mental health. The family
OL,9,Fwere unaware of this for a year
OL,10,Ffollowing her death.
OL,12,FAs part of their campaign for a
OL,13,Fstronger duty of care from
OL,14,Funiversities, they are now calling for
OL,15,Fan "opt-out" system, where a student
OL,16,Fnominates a trusted person the
OL,17,Funiversity can contact if a student is
OL,18,Ffacing difficult circumstances.
OL,19,FCurrently, universities have no legal
OL,20,Fobligation to do this for students of
OL,21,F18 years of age or older.
